Mortgage Foreclosures Treasurers Tax Sales Treasurers Tax LIEN Sales Go to Bottom Go to Top

Active = Still scheduled for sale      Sold = The property sold on the "Sale Date"
Cancelled * = Sale cancelled by the Court No Bid * = There were no bid on the "Sale Date"
DCR = Advertised in the Daily Court Reporter * =May or may not come up again
This web site is provided as a public service and updated weekly, however, the information provided is limited and not required by law. The legally mandated description of properties is published in the in the DAYTON DAILY NEWS / DAILY COURT REPORTER. Employees of the Sheriff's Office are not permitted to give legal advice.
MORTGAGE FORECLOSURE
Effective September, 11, 2008: Terms of Sale: The successful bidder must deposit 10% of the purchase price plus transfer and recording fees immediately following the sale. We will accept cash, certified check or a personal check with proper ID and signed in our presence for the deposit. The personal check must be drawn off of a local bank. The required 10% deposit is waived where the purchaser is the first lienholder. The unpaid balance of the purchase price must be paid to the Montgomery County Sheriff by certified or cashier's check within thirty (30) days of the filing of the confirmation entry. The plaintiffs' attorney will prepare the confirmation entry and the deed. The Montgomery County Sheriff's Office will transfer and record all deeds within 14 days of receiving the deed, confirmation entry and final payment. The purchaser may be responsible for paying the transfer, recording and conveyance fees for cases purchased at the Sheriff Sale.

TREASURER'S TAX SALES
Effective September, 11, 2008: Terms of Sale: The successful bidder must deposit $1,000.00 PLUS TRANSFER AND RECORDING FEES immediately following the sale. We will accept cash, certified check or a personal check with proper ID and signed in our presence for the deposit. The personal check must be drawn off of a local bank. The unpaid balance must be paid to the Montgomery County Sheriff by certified or cashier's check within thirty (30) days from the date the confirmation of sale is filed by the plaintiff's attorney. All deeds will be prepared by the attorney of record and recorded by the Montgomery County Sheriff's Office within 14 days of receiving final payment from the purchaser.

TREASURER'S TAX LIEN SALES
Effective September, 11, 2008: Terms of Sale: The successful bidder must deposit $1,000.00 PLUS TRANSFER AND RECORDING FEES immediately following the sale. We will accept cash, certified check or a personal check with proper ID and signed in our presence for the deposit. The personal check must be drawn off of a local bank. The unpaid balance must be paid to the Montgomery County Sheriff by certified or cashier's check within thirty (30) days from the date the confirmation of sale is filed by the plaintiff's attorney. All deeds will be prepared by the attorney of record and recorded by the Montgomery County Sheriff's Office within 14 days of receiving final payment from the purchaser.
In 1997, the State of Ohio passed a law allowing counties in Ohio with a population greater than 200,000 to sell tax lien certificates on certified tax delinquent properties in the county (Ohio Revised Code sections 5721.30 through 5721.43). The liens, consisting of the delinquent tax dollar amount plus fees, penalties, and interest, are sold in large bundles to qualified financial lenders. After one year, if the owner fails to redeem the lien (does not pay the lien holder the taxes, fees, and interest owed) the financial institution has the right to foreclose on the property. The following properties have been foreclosed on by the financial institution owning the lien and are listed for sale as follows:
